    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-10-13T07:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-10-13T07:30:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <head>64. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d64fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country File,
                        Vietnam, <gloss target="#t_HARVAN1">HARVAN</gloss>/Double Plus, Vol. I.
                        Secret; Immediate; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1">Nodis</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_HARVAN1">HARVAN</gloss>/Double Plus. Received at 9:35
                        a.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Saigon</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-10-13T12:30:00+00:00">October 13, 1968,
                        1230Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40178. Subject: Meeting with <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> concurs in instructions to be
                        given <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>-<persName
                            corresp="#p_VCR1">Vance</persName>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGC1">General Abrams</persName>, Amb <persName
                            corresp="#p_BSR1">Berger</persName> and I had hour and a half meeting
                        with him tonight. We went over developments of last four days starting with
                        October 9 tea break, and gave him orally paraphrased version of instructions
                        and how we intended to proceed on all fronts.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGC1">Abrams</persName> outlined military situation
                        and implications of a bombing cessation on military position, and we
                        exchanged views as to what military or other reasons prompted Hanoi to shift
                        to negotiations. <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> asked whether
                        we intended to make reference to infiltration, and we said no and <persName
                            corresp="#p_AGC1">Abrams</persName> and I persuaded him that we can
                        handle whatever they send down. <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName>
                        thought that if Hanoi is serious in these negotiations they will soon
                        propose cease-fire.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>We then together sketched out the sequence of next moves: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> agrees to
                                instructions.</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>We notify other contributors.</item>
                            <label>C.</label>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>-<persName
                                    corresp="#p_VCR1">Vance</persName> put proposals to Hanoi at
                                Paris.</item>
                            <label>D.</label>
                            <item>If Hanoi accepts them, Washington and Saigon work out timing for
                                cessation, and date of meeting which <gloss target="#t_GVN1"
                                    >GVN</gloss> will join.</item>
                            <label>E.</label>
                            <item>Joint <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName>-<persName
                                    corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> announcement made that
                                attacks on North stopped in effort to find basis for peaceful
                                settlement. <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> understands
                                fully that we will not use words like reciprocal actions, agreement
                                of Hanoi, etc., and need for secrecy.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> will inform a few key
                        colleagues tomorrow of latest developments and his decision.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>Foregoing are bare-bones. Will send fuller report tomorrow.<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d64fn2">The full report of the conversation was transmitted in
                            telegram 40220 from Saigon, October 14. (Ibid.)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BE2">
                            <hi rend="strong">Bunker</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
